result.formatted_address: 175 Lockhart Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: New Korean BBQ Restaurant

reviews.text: Decent place with a good selection of food. Price wise it is reasonable for the location. It is a big restaurant, so expect noise levels to be high. Yes, they have sushi and seafood selections, but their beef, pork and chicken selection is wanting somewhat. Drinks are cheap (22HKD for Heineken is great).
Good selection of meat and vegetables. Fair price for an all you can eat Korean BBQ
Nice food, nice prices. Service could be way friendlier.

Great BBQ spot. There is seafood as well as sushi which I've never seen at a Korean BBQ spot before but I was definitely not complaining. Come hungry and you will eat unlimited for 90 minutes. Large selection of meat and veggies as well as a couple soups. Only complaint was that they wouldn't change the grill when it became quite dirty from all the meat.

Korean buffet for around 200hkd a head. Always fun with friends and affordable. Also, ice-cream is included, which is oddly what I consider the best bit. I'm deducting a star because I watched a staff member take a slash and not wash his hands.
